# Phase 8: Layout, Margins & Position Controls Walkthrough

Phase 8 has been successfully completed! KeryxPro now features independent, comprehensive, 2D layout constraints for both the main presentation content ("Body") and subtitles ("Title").

## What We Changed

### 1. Unified 3x3 Alignment Grids
We replaced the basic position dropdowns with a **3x3 Alignment Grid**.
* **Visual Selection**: You can easily visualize where text will anchor to by clicking exactly which zone of the screen is desired.
* **Smart Defaults**: As requested, the Title defaults to the bottom-center block, while the Body defaults to dead-center.

### 2. Precise Boundary Margins (2x2 Matrix)
Instead of a single slider defining an ambiguous "Margin", every layer now respects true 4-way independent margins.
* **Margin Matrix UI**: A sleek matrix of `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, and `Right` parameters that intuitively map to the screen edges via blue border highlights on the UI graphics next to them. 
* **Complete Flexibility**: You can manually input `px` constraints directly. Need the title to jut exactly 60px away from the left edge? You can type that directly. It also fully supports negative margin inputs as you requested!

### 3. Layer Visibility Toggles
* A master checkbox is now present beside the "Title" layer block. Disabling it cleanly hides the title entirely from the presentation.

### 4. Rendering Accuracy
* **Stack Upgrades**: Underneath everything, the rendering engine was upgraded from rigid linear tracking (`Column`) to isolated mapping (`Stack`). The `live_projector_pane` and `presentation_settings_dialog` exactly mirror these precision anchors dynamically.

> [!TIP]
> Play around with inputting negative `px` boundaries onto your alignment grid anchors to shift visuals creatively outside their bounding boxes!
